`★ Insight ─────────────────────────────────────`
The existing `wildTreeRegrowth.ts` is a pure timer-based system that tracks when individual grid positions should regrow. The chunk-based update needs to add a parallel *probability-based* spawning layer: each tick, for each visited chunk with room for trees, roll against a seasonal spawn chance. The two layers are complementary — the timer (position-specific) and the ecology tick (chunk-level) can coexist.
`─────────────────────────────────────────────────`

