The `shouldSpawnWildTree` function uses a unique `scopedRNG` key per (chunkX, chunkZ, currentDay) triple. This guarantees that re-running the tick for the same day produces identical results (deterministic replay), while a different day or different chunk gets a statistically independent roll. This is the standard codebase pattern for seeded procedural decisions.
